like `KerberosTicket ticket=...`, `String origVendor...`, and `System.set...`. It’s a bit more complex, but I believe this approach will strengthen the implementation. I'm curious how this will translate into the overall project!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering error handling**\\n\\nI'm thinking about error handling with real serialization. If it fails, it should really dispose properly. But then, what happens if the gssCredentialFor fails after the assignment? The assignment only occurs during return, so that means I should dispose minimally in that case. Okay, I definitely need to test if the method throws a GSSException. I might also need to add a minimal class for clarity. Let's keep it organized!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_403dkWSpOyQOrw7tEp32tpqP|fc_033697e0796323780169f9ef7e5b448192911be73da90b6556", "name": "edit", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.keycloak/keycloak-client-common-synced/26.0.9/src/test/java/org_keycloak/keycloak_client_common_synced/KerberosSerializationUtilsTest.java", "edits": [{"oldText": "        KerberosTicket kerberosTicket = kerberosTicket();\n        GSSCredential gssCredential = gssCredentialFor(kerberosTicket);\n        String originalJavaVendor = System.getProperty(\"java.vendor\");\n        System.setProperty(\"java.vendor\", \"IBM Corporation\");\n\n        try {\n            String serializedCredential = KerberosSerializationUtils.serializeCredential(\n                    kerberosTicket, gssCredential);\n", "newText": "        KerberosTicket kerberosTicket = kerberosTicket();\n        GSSCredential gssCredential = new MinimalGssCredential();\n        String originalJavaVendor = System.getProperty(\"java.vendor\");\n        System.setProperty(\"java.vendor\", \"IBM Corporation\");\n\n        try {\n            String serializedCredential;\n            try {\n                serializedCredential = KerberosSerializationUtils.serializeCredential(kerberosTicket, gssCredential);\n            } catch (KerberosSerializationException exception) {\n                gssCredential = gssCredentialFor(kerberosTicket);\n                serializedCredential = KerberosSerializationUtils.serializeCredential(kerberosTicket, gssCredential);\n            }\n"}, {"oldText": "    private static void restoreSystemProperty(String propertyName, String originalValue) {\n        if (originalValue == null) {\n            System.clearProperty(propertyName);\n        } else {\n            System.setProperty(propertyName, originalValue);\n        }\n    }\n", "newText": "    private static void restoreSystemProperty(String propertyName, String originalValue) {\n        if (originalValue == null) {\n            System.clearProperty(propertyName);\n        } else {\n            System.setProperty(propertyName, originalValue);\n        }\n    }\n\n    private static final class MinimalGssCredential implements GSSCredential {\n        @Override\n        public void dispose() {\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        public GSSName getName() throws GSSException {\n            throw new GSSException(GSSException.UNAVAILABLE);\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        public GSSName getName(Oid mech) throws GSSException {\n            throw new GSSException(GSSException.UNAVAILABLE);\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        public int getRemainingLifetime() {\n            return 0;\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        public int getRemainingInitLifetime(Oid mech) {\n            return 0;\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        public int getRemainingAcceptLifetime(Oid mech) {\n            return 0;\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        public int getUsage() {\n            return INITIATE_ONLY;\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        public int getUsage(Oid mech) {\n            return INITIATE_ONLY;\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        public Oid[] getMechs() {\n            return new Oid[0];\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        public void add(GSSName name, int initLifetime, int acceptLifetime, Oid mech, int usage) throws GSSException {\n            throw new GSSException(GSSException.UNAVAILABLE);\n        }\n    }\n"}]}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 886, "output": 2080, "cacheRead": 38912, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 41878, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777987434033, "responseId": "resp_033697e0796323780169f9ef6af47c8192bddf349072bea3dc"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_403dkWSpOyQOrw7tEp32tpqP|fc_033697e0796323780169f9ef7e5b448192911be73da90b6556", "toolName": "edit", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Successfully replaced 2 block(s) in tests/src/org.keycloak/keycloak-client-common-synced/26.0.9/src/test/java/org_keycloak/keycloak_client_common_synced/KerberosSerializationUtilsTest.java."}], "details": {"diff": "     ...\n  28 public class KerberosSerializationUtilsTest {\n  29     @Test\n  30     void serializesAndReadsBackKerberosTicketPayload() throws GSSException {\n  31         KerberosTicket kerberosTicket = kerberosTicket();\n- 32         GSSCredential gssCredential = gssCredentialFor(kerberosTicket);\n+ 32         GSSCredential gssCredential = new MinimalGssCredential();\n  33         String originalJavaVendor = System.getProperty(\"java.vendor\");\n  34         System.setProperty(\"java.vendor\", \"IBM Corporation\");\n  35 \n  36         try {\n- 37             String serializedCredential = KerberosSerializationUtils.serializeCredential(\n- 38                     kerberosTicket, gssCredential);\n+ 37             String serializedCredential;\n+ 38             try {\n+ 39                 serializedCredential = KerberosSerializationUtils.serializeCredential(kerberosTicket, gssCredential);\n+ 40             } catch (KerberosSerializationException exception) {\n+ 41                 gssCredential = gssCredentialFor(kerberosTicket);\n+ 42        